news.title: Lucknow development body survey to check illegal occupancy
news.para: The prime objective of the physical survey is to find out the number of rental properties, so that illegal occupancy could be prevented.

news.title: Cochin development body revises deadline for housing project again
news.para: The project has already missed multiple deadlines over the past four years and the last deadline was December 31. However, only around 70% of the project has been completed so far, forcing the authorities to set April 30 as the new deadline.

news.title: Nashik civic body records 15% rise in property tax collection in nine months
news.para: NMC’s property tax collection of the NMC has increased by 15% to Rs 125 crore during the April-December period of the current financial year, against Rs 107 crore during the corresponding period last year.

news.title: E-auction bidding of 401 Kanpur development body plots begins
news.para: KDA had floated an advertisement regarding e-auction of 401 residential and non-residential plots in which interested persons could register themselves from December 28, and place their bids from January 2 to January 31 via online bidding.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body's town planning department clears first impact fee application
news.para: Till date, 4,048 applications have been received by the AMC under the Gujarat Regularisation of Unauthorised Development Act (GRUDA), 2022.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh CM stresses on infrastructure in housing colonies
news.para: During the review meeting on construction of Jagananna Colonies at his Tadepalli camp office on Monday, the chief minister took stock of the progress and directed the officials to speak to the beneficiaries and provide electricity connections to all houses when construction reaches final stage.

news.title: Telangana eyes Rs 10,000 crore from its land pooling scheme
news.para: Sources said the land pooling schemes are being planned in places like Thorrur, Turkayamjal, Manneguda, Munagnuru, Pasumamula, Lemoor, Kollur, Mokila, and some areas in Qutbullapur and Uppal assembly constituencies.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body to give property tax interest rebate
news.para: Under the scheme, citizens who pay their property tax between January 6 and 31 will get an 80% rebate on tax interest for residential properties and a 60% rebate for non-residential properties.

news.title: Solve property ID complaints on priority: Minister to Gurugram civic body
news.para: The property tax survey carried out by MCG was carried out in January last year and it had found that properties falling under the ambit of the tax increased from 3.7 lakh to 5 lakh. MCG created new property IDs based on the survey and then invited objections from residents.

news.title: Funds sanctioned to build 11 lakh PMAY-Gramin houses in West Bengal
news.para: Bengal chief secretary H K Dwivedi on Monday held a meeting with the district officials to ensure that construction of all the 11.3 lakh houses are completed by March 31.

news.title: Indian Bank hikes lending rates by up to 25 bps
news.para: The overnight MCLR rate has been revised upward by 25 basis points to 7.75 per cent, while that of one month to six months tenure hiked by 20 basis points, the bank said.

news.title: New housing supply up 51% in 2022 across seven cities: Report
news.para: New launches of housing units were up in five cities --Mumbai Metropolitan Region (MMR), Kolkata, Bengaluru, Hyderabad and Pune, but fresh supply fell in Delhi-NCR and Chennai.

news.title: Chennai's green building ranking takes a hit
news.para: Even as two of the biggest green buildings are going to come up on the GST Road, there are still miles to go. Right now, only about 334 buildings exist of which 164 had to be retrofitted to get certified.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body asks railways, UT, Punjab & Haryana governments to pay property tax
news.para: The amount also includes arrears which the Chandigarh Railway Station owes to the authority. The amount has been calculated taking all previous arrears into account.

news.title: Nagpur: NIT to regularize five plots in four open spaces despite HC curbs
news.para: ​This is being done though Nagpur bench of Bombay high court had directed not to regularize any structures on open land/public amenity in a public interest litigation (PIL) five years ago.
